		<div class="comment-body"><p>In regards to Open/Concealed Carry:</p>
<p>I live in a State where we do not have &#8220;open or concealed&#8221; we just have a Carry Permit&#8211;meaning either.  While overall, I prefer Concealed carry, I think it is VITAL to have open carry for the reasons Jack mentioned about &#8220;Brandishing.&#8221;</p>
<p>Depending on where you are and the mentality of Law enforcement or the public, you can get into major trouble if you simply move in the wrong way and someone happens to view your firearm.  Get a person with an agenda and a police officer who isn&#8217;t a supporter of citizens&#8217; rights, and you can wind up with a major hassle or legal trouble.</p>
<p>So, I hope everyone can get universal carry laws passed in your States.</p>
